attributes.background:
In view of the excessive travel explenses being claimed by Members of Parliement, we the undersigned petition the Prime Minister to arrange for them to be restricted in the following ways:
1. Motoring expenses will be paid only against receipts for petrol, diesel or other fuel at the rate of three times the total expenditure less the current fuel tax and current VAT paid by all motorists;

2. Flying expenses to be paid  only against receipts at the rate of three times for economy class travel less the airport, insurance and other taxes and surcharges the public pays;

3. No travel claims to exceed £2000 per member per annum.

4. Details of amounts paid in Travel Expenses to each MP to be published annually one week after the Budget and Finance Bill.
